This page is meant to be a place to collect information about the recently published IPCC assessment report AR5. Feel free to add! (NOTE: Depending on how many entries this page will see, we may subdivide it into meaningful sections)

#IPCC-AR5 -- Basic Resources  
* [Climate Change 2013](http://www.climatechange2013.org/): The new homepage of Working Group I: The Physical Science Basis.

* [Summary for Policymakers](http://www.climatechange2013.org/images/uploads/WGIAR5-SPM_Approved27Sep2013.pdf) of "Working Group I: The Physical Science Basis", finalized and released on 27 Sept 2013.

* [Fifth Assessment Report on Wikipedia](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IPCC_Fifth_Assessment_Report)

* [Summary for Policymakers (SPM) broken into sections](http://www.climatescience.org.au/content/382-summary-policymakers) - from Climate System Science from the Australian Research Council.

* [Report of the Earth Negotiation Bulletin](http://www.iisd.ca/vol12/enb12581e.html) on the 12th session of Working Group I (WGI) of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) finalizing its report.

#IPCC-AR5 -- Reactions and Analyses
* [BBC Panel Discussion on IPCC5](http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03brkds). Participants: Professor Julia Slingo, UK Met Office Chief Scientist; Sir Mark Walport, UK Government Chief Scientific Adviser; Dr. Bjorn Lomborg, Author of "The Skeptical Environmentalist"; Professor Mike Hulme, Professor of Climate and Culture, King's College London; Mark Lynas, Author and environmentalist; Tony Grayling, Head of Climate Change and Communities, UK Environment Agency.

* [IPCC report underlines the need for climate action](http://www.abc.net.au/environment/articles/2013/09/27/3857704.htm) - from ABC Environment, written by Michael Mann and Dana Nuccitelli.

* [The new IPCC climate report](http://www.realclimate.org/index.php/archives/2013/09/the-new-ipcc-climate-report/) - from RealClimate, written by Stefan Rahmstorf.

* [Why is the IPCC AR5 so much more confident in human-caused global warming?](http://skepticalscience.com/ipcc-ar5-human-caused-global-warming-confidence.html) - from Skeptical Science, written by Dana Nuccitelli.

* [Climate Change: Action, Trends and Implications for Business – The IPCC’s Fifth Assessment Report, Working Group 1](http://www.cpsl.cam.ac.uk/Resources/Climate-and-Energy/Understanding-the-UN-Climate-Science-Reports.aspx#sthash.rLQqe1fP.dpuf) - from University of Cambridge, especially the graphic is a good summary of the IPCC Report suggested pathways and their implications.
